They are latin letters, not English letters. As a compromise, I've replaced this by "uppercase (from A to Z) and lowercase (from a to z) letters";

A digit can be repeated, and I've added a test case representing that. The maximum of characters in the output is directly related to the limit on the input, and experimentally, I've found that the limit of characters that can be emitted given a 249 char maximum is 15625. Not really sure how this limit is really useful to add to the constraints though, so I'd prefer not to.

All other reviews have been fixed, thanks :)
